***********************************************
* JFREEREPORT 0.7.2 INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS *
***********************************************

Written by David Gilbert, 15 May 2002.

1. INTRODUCTION
---------------
This document describes how to download and install the latest version
of JFreeReport (0.7.2).  The procedure has changed from the previous
version, as the release is now being packaged up by Thomas Morgner,
the new Project Leader for JFreeReport.

2. DOWNLOAD
-----------
You can download the latest version of JFreeReport from the
JFreeReport project page on SourceForge:

http://sourceforge.net/projects/jfreereport

You need to download all of the following files (I'd recommend saving
them to a new directory called jfreereport-0.7.2):

- jfreereport-0.7.2.jar     : the JFreeReport runtime jar file;
- jfreereport-res-0.7.2.jar : icons and other resources;
- jfreereport-src-0.7.2.jar : source code files;
- pixie.jar                 : the Pixie runtime jar file;
- pixie-res.jar             : resources for Pixie;
- pixie-src.jar             : Pixie source code;
- libs.jar                  : runtime jar files for the libraries used
                              by JFreeReport.

3. UNPACKING
------------
You need to unpack some of the jar files in order to run the
demonstration application.

First, create a subdirectory called resources, within the
jfreereport-0.7.2 directory that you created.  Move the
jfreereport-res-0.7.2.jar file to this new subdirectory, then run the
jar utility to unpack the files:

jar -xvf jfreereport-res-0.7.2.jar

Second, create a subdirectory called libs within the
jfreereport-0.7.2 directory.  Move the libs.zip file to this new
subdirectory, and unzip it:

unzip libs.zip

This extracts the following jar files:

gnujaxp.jar
iText.jar
jcommon-0.6.1.jar
junit.jar
pixie.jar

As an optional last step, create a subdirectory called source within
the jfreereport-0.7.2 directory.  Move the jfreereport-src-0.7.2.jar
and pixie-src.jar files to this new subdirectory, then run the jar
utility to unpack the files:

jar -xvf jfreereport-src-0.7.2.jar
jar -xvf pixie-src.jar

This extracts all the source code files.

4. RUNNING THE DEMONSTRATION APPLICATION
----------------------------------------
To run the demonstration application, type the following command from
the jfreereport-0.7.2 directory:

java -classpath
jfreereport-0.7.2.jar:libs/jcommon-0.6.1.jar:libs/gnujaxp.jar:libs/iText.jar:libs/pixie.jar:./resources
com.jrefinery.report.demo.JFreeReportDemo

Note that the above command should be entered on a single command
line.  On Windows, substitute a semi-colon for the colon as the path
separator in the classpath setting, and use backslashes instead of
forward slashes.

5. FEEDBACK
-----------
Please post your feedback in the JFreeReport forum at:

http://www.object-refinery.com/jfreereport/index.html
